# expected-to-throw
# Tests that cross-validation of linked fields on same concrete type
# (non-mutually-exclusive) correctly detects argument conflicts at
# nested levels. Both selections are on the same type (User), so
# the sub-field argument difference is a real conflict.
query CrossValidationNestedArgConflict {
  me {
    feedback {
      author {
        profilePicture(size: 100) {
          uri
        }
      }
    }
    feedback {
      author {
        profilePicture(size: 200) {
          uri
        }
      }
    }
  }
}
==================================== ERROR ====================================
✖︎ Expected all fields on the same parent with the name or alias `profilePicture` to have the same argument values after applying fragment arguments. This field has the applied argument values: (size: 100). If the same field appears with different arguments, use an alias to distinguish them, e.g. `myAlias: profilePicture(...)`.

